# Web client

Owner: **presentation**. Rules live in `game-engine`.

## Stores

| Store | May hold |
|-------|----------|
| `gameStore` | `GameState` copy; calls engine in actions |
| `motionStore` | Visual cues only (`play`, `draw`, `pendingPlayExit`) |
| `audioStore` | Settings + unlock |

Forbidden: duplicate gameplay flags; rule logic in `useEffect`.

## Card UX (contract)

- `CardBar` + `HandDirectiveCard`: click plays card
- `PlayedCards`: active **assets** only
- `DirectiveArchive`: played **events** only
- Use `DirectiveCard` variants — do not fork new card shells

## Motion

- Do not block input for animations
- No Framer `layout` on hand strip
- `transform` / `opacity` only

## Engine boundary

```typescript
const res = playCard(library, get().state, cardId);
if (!res.ok) { set({ error: res.error }); return; }
set({ state: res.state, ... });
```

## Verification

`cd apps/web && npm run build && npm run lint`

## Forbidden

- `Math.random()` for game outcomes
- Parsing `cards.json` in components (use library Map)
- New features in `packages/ui`
